summary: I watched the coming out video that Dan posted. It's nice to have representation. The thing that bothers me though is the...
body:
I watched the coming out video that Dan posted. It’s nice to have representation. The thing that bothers me though is the pressure that people put on others to constantly be an open book. Just because someone presents a certain way on camera doesn’t mean they are always that way. These are real people doing their jobs. ‘Fans’ and strangers of the internet should not be trying to force relationships and sending nsfw matterial without consent. If you do this kind of bullshit to a random person on the street law enforcement would get involved. Just because you ate at a restaurant once doesn’t mean you have the right to dig through their kitchen drawer for chips. Let people live their lives. They will show what they want, and as viewers we should not pester or whine, and throwing rocks is not a healthy form of encouragement.

Please for the love of God, do your best to be respectful and patient. These are real people with real lives, humans have limits, give them space to breathe.

Nobody should have to feel forced to come out of the closet. Nobody should have to feel forced into a relationship. You control yourself and not anybody else.
